quran[25]{c,v,t}:
  14,28,Have you not seen those ňĻdisbelieversňļ who meet God‚Äôs favours with ingratitude and lead their own people to their doom
  14,29,In Hell they will burn. What an evil place for settlement
  14,30,"They set up equals to God to mislead ňĻothersňļ from His Way. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúEnjoy yourselves! Surely your destination is the Fire.‚ÄĚ"
  14,31,Tell My believing servants to establish prayer and donate from what We have provided for them‚ÄĒopenly and secretly‚ÄĒbefore the arrival of a Day in which there will be no ransom or friendly connections
  14,32,"It is God Who created the heavens and the earth and sends down rain from the sky, causing fruits to grow as a provision for you. He has subjected the ships for your service, sailing through the sea by His command, and has subjected the rivers for you"
  14,33,"He has ňĻalsoňļ subjected for you the sun and the moon, both constantly orbiting, and has subjected the day and night for you"
  14,34,"And He has granted you all that you asked Him for. If you tried to count God‚Äôs blessings, you would never be able to number them. Indeed humankind is truly unfair, ňĻtotallyňļ ungrateful"
  14,35,"ňĻRememberňļ when Abraham prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Make this city ňĻof Meccaňļ secure, and keep me and my children away from the worship of idols"
  14,36,"My Lord! They have caused many people to go astray. So whoever follows me is with me, and whoever disobeys me‚ÄĒthen surely You are ňĻstillňļ All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  14,37,"Our Lord! I have settled some of my offspring in a barren valley, near Your Sacred House, our Lord, so that they may establish prayer. So make the hearts of ňĻbelievingňļ people incline towards them and provide them with fruits, so perhaps they will be thankful"
  14,38,Our Lord! You certainly know what we conceal and what we reveal. Nothing on earth or in heaven is hidden from God
  14,39,All praise is for God who has blessed me with Ishmael and Isaac in my old age. My Lord is indeed the Hearer of ňĻallňļ prayers
  14,40,My Lord! Make me and those ňĻbelieversňļ of my descendants keep up prayer. Our Lord! Accept my prayers
  14,41,"Our Lord! Forgive me, my parents, and the believers on the Day when the judgment will come to pass.‚ÄĚ"
  14,42,Do not think ňĻO Prophetňļ that God is unaware of what the wrongdoers do. He only delays them until a Day when ňĻtheirňļ eyes will stare in horror‚ÄĒ
  14,43,"rushing forth, heads raised, never blinking, hearts void"
  14,44,"And warn the people of the Day when the punishment will overtake ňĻthe wicked amongňļ them, and the wrongdoers will cry, ‚ÄúOur Lord! Delay us for a little while. We will respond to Your call and follow the messengers!‚ÄĚ ňĻIt will be said,ňļ ‚ÄúDid you not swear before that you would never be removed ňĻto the next lifeňļ?‚ÄĚ"
  14,45,"You passed by the ruins of those ňĻdestroyed peoplesňļ who had wronged themselves.¬†It was made clear to you how We dealt with them, and We gave you ňĻmanyňļ examples"
  14,46,"They devised every plot, which was fully known to God, but their plotting was not enough to ňĻevenňļ overpower mountains ňĻlet alone Godňļ"
  14,47,"So do not think ňĻO Prophetňļ that God will fail to keep His promise to His messengers. God is indeed Almighty, capable of punishment"
  14,48,"ňĻWatch forňļ the Day ňĻwhenňļ the earth will be changed into a different earth and the heavens as well, and all will appear before God‚ÄĒthe One, the Supreme"
  14,49,On that Day you will see the wicked bound together in chains
  14,50,"with garments of tar, and their faces covered with flames"
  14,51,"As such, God will reward every soul for what it has committed. Surely God is swift in reckoning"
  14,52,"This ňĻQuranňļ is a ňĻsufficientňļ message for humanity so that they may take it as a warning and know that there is only One God, and so that people of reason may be mindful"